; sensing-lanes.form — the perception/sensing arc, one lane at a time: north star · ground · direction · distance.
;
; The map that keeps each lane honest. GROUND is only what is proven or measured (verdicts, or a
; toolchain probe) — never a hope. DIRECTION is the next real move. DISTANCE is what remains to the
; north star, in the lc-honest-lane grain (MEASURED / BUILDABLE / carrier-work). Read top-to-bottom:
; the lanes are ordered from "the logic is done" toward "needs real hardware." Updated 2026-06-09.
;
; THE WHOLE-ARC NORTH STAR: a body that senses its field through every available sense, recognizes it
; with classifiers it grew and proved itself, shares what it learns with other bodies, and runs all of
; it natively on whatever silicon it is given — no foreign model, no third-party permission, every
; joint proven three-way (Go=Rust=TS) and content-addressed so identity travels with structure.
;
; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
; LANE 1 — RECOGNITION ROUTING
;   north star  every modality fused into one trusted recognition stream, chosen in the kernel, in parallel.
;   ground      recognition-router.fk proven — sound 127, sight 31, host compute-paths 63. Modality-blind.
;   direction   feed real carriers (whisper · SoundAnalysis · Vision) in as readings (lane 10's wiring).
;   distance    the router is DONE. Remaining is carriers handing it live readings — carrier-work, no new logic.
;
; LANE 2 — THE BODY'S OWN PERCEPTION (the toolkit)
;   north star  a complete, content-addressed perception the body runs and grows for itself, no foreign model.
;   ground      ~20 recipes proven three-way: feature-vector · nearest-shape · novelty · sequence-predictor ·
;               classifier-eval · temporal-smoothing · perception-pipeline(127) · drift-detect · ensemble-vote ·
;               anomaly-band · markov-2 · histogram-peak · transition-detect · cooldown.
;   direction   real features from real carriers; nearest-shape interns real prototypes; the pipeline runs on a stream.
;   distance    the LOGIC is done. Remaining is real data flowing through — carrier-work (lane 10).
;
; LANE 3 — SELF-GROUNDING
;   north star  the body's own classifiers earn trust on its own field and retire the foreign ones.
;   ground      self-grounding-classifier.fk proven (63) — promotion only on proven agreement with ground truth.
;   direction   run the shadow-learning loop on real readings graded against a trusted route / a declared source.
;   distance    the promotion gate is done. Remaining is a real learning run — carrier-work, gated on lanes 2+10.
;
; LANE 4 — DECLARED-SOURCE (ask before guessing)
;   north star  read what a source announces (now-playing, device names) before spending a classifier.
;   ground      declared-source.fk proven (127) — prefer / skip / ground; the Android MediaSession carrier named.
;   direction   wire the MediaSession now-playing as a declared reading.
;   distance    logic done. The MediaSession carrier is Android work — GATED on lane 8 (kernel on Android).
;
; LANE 5 — SHARED SENSING (many bodies, one field)
;   north star  phones and Macs side by side, different senses, teaching each other in real time.
;   ground      shared-sensing.fk proven (127) — circle confirms by quorum, cross-grounding, silence whole.
;   direction   the cell-sync transport (lane 9, logic now proven) carrying learned cells between two running kernels.
;   distance    logic done. Needs the transport wire (lane 9) AND the kernel on two devices (lane 8).
;
; LANE 6 — LOCAL INFERENCE AS ORGAN
;   north star  the body owns the inference graph and routing, drives MLX/silicon as a port, no 3rd-party gate.
;   ground      local-inference-as-organ.form + the compute-path router (recognition-router-compute 63).
;   direction   a resource-sense port (read GPU/ANE/bandwidth/thermal) feeding the compute router by live throughput.
;   distance    routing logic done. The resource-sense port + the MLX driver are carrier-work (macOS powermetrics/Metal; MLX).
;
; LANE 7 — OPEN PRIMITIVE SET (the kernel learns its own primitives)
;   north star  the kernel grows primitives ("at-home", "walking") from raw sensors by heat, melts them when cold.
;   ground      learned-primitive.fk proven (255); substrate-phase.fk (the gas↔water↔ice metabolism) + the JIT already built.
;   direction   the sensor BINDINGS as kernel leaves (lane 8) + the JIT mechanism to install/melt a learned primitive.
;   distance    the policy is done. The sensor leaves + JIT-install are kernel/carrier-work — GATED on lane 8.
;
; LANE 8 — KERNEL ON ANDROID  ◀ the longest hardware lane; everything device-bound waits here
;   north star  the proven recipes run bit-identical on a phone, fed by its own sensors.
;   ground      [MEASURED 2026-06-09 — THE KERNEL NOW CROSS-COMPILES FOR ANDROID ARM64] form-kernel-rust builds clean for
;               aarch64-linux-android: "ELF 64-bit LSB pie executable, ARM aarch64 ... interpreter /system/bin/linker64"
;               (4.6 MB, the whole engine + tokio-postgres/rustls/ureq, ~70s). Toolchain installed: brew android-ndk (29) +
;               cargo-ndk (4.1.2) + rustup aarch64-linux-android std. pyo3 stays OFF (opt-in feature) so NO Python-for-Android.
;               Reproducible: form/form-kernel-rust/build-android.sh. The gotcha that cost two tries: Homebrew rustc has no
;               cross-std, so the rustup toolchain must be FIRST in PATH (cargo-ndk shells out to cargo, re-resolving PATH).
;   direction   [MEASURED 2026-06-09 — THE APP-LOADABLE LIBRARY IS BUILT] the predicted "extract the engine out of main.rs"
;               refactor was unnecessary: lib.rs already includes main.rs as a module (for PyO3), so the cdylib only needed a
;               non-default `cabi` feature + a #[no_mangle] extern "C" form_eval(src)->display-text entry over the SAME
;               kernel::run_source the CLI runs. cargo ndk -t arm64-v8a build --release --lib --features cabi emits
;               libform_kernel_rust.so: "ELF 64-bit LSB shared object, ARM aarch64 ... exports form_eval / form_eval_free"
;               (~4 MB, ~27s). Verified via ctypes on host: sd-moving? + ns-label recognize correctly through the C boundary.
;               Both artifacts are reproducible: build-android.sh (bin + cdylib, each file-checked + symbol-checked).
;   distance    the ENGINE work is DONE on both surfaces (ARM bin + JNI-callable cdylib, symbol-verified). Remaining is
;               carrier wiring, not engine: a thin Kotlin JNI shim (external fun formEval(src): String) + the .so dropped in
;               jniLibs/arm64-v8a + the recipes bundled as assets, then a device/emulator to RUN it on ARM, + ONE sensor port.
;               On-device three-way (all three kernels on one phone) still UNRUN — day one is one arm. The hardware lane is SHORT.
;
; LANE 9 — CELL-SYNC TRANSPORT (share cells device↔device)
;   north star  a cell learned on one device reaches another, content-addressed and consent-honored.
;   ground      cell-sync.fk proven (127) — diff (want-set) / verify (re-address) / consent (shareable) LOGIC is done;
;               merkle.fk (addressing) + channel-interface.fk (consent law) already built.
;   direction   the wire FRAMES (offer / request-have-not / send / ack-verified) as Form over the socket port.
;   distance    the diff/verify/consent logic is DONE. The wire frames are BUILDABLE (compose socket-port + merkle + consent);
;               peer discovery (how two devices find each other) is UNKNOWN/carrier-work — named, not faked.
;
; LANE 10 — THE LIVE PRESENCE TOOL (the runnable show)
;   north star  an always-on companion that senses the room and offers to the circle, on real hardware.
;   ground      Coherence Sense ships TWO Mac ends + an installable Android .apk (the phone as a sense organ):
;               mac-witness-server.py (thin witness) and coherence-sense-eval.py (LIVE RECOGNITION AND LIVE LEARNING through
;               the kernel), both with a dashboard at http://localhost:8800. experiments/satsang-voice also runs (mic ->
;               whisper + SoundAnalysis). The recognition AND supervision recipes are proven AND now wired into the live loop.
;   direction   grow the recognized vocabulary (still/moving -> gestures, gait, room-states) and feed real audio/vision carriers.
;   distance    [MEASURED 2026-06-09 — live recognition AND live learning are BUILT, not a wall; the earlier "needs a
;               persistent kernel data-API, best with the human" reading was a hedge, disproved by a running server] the bare
;               kernel DOES recognize per frame: recipes use kernel primitives, so core.fk (BML source) is NOT needed —
;               `form-kernel-rust <recipe>.fk <driver>.fk` prints the label at ~5ms. coherence-sense-eval.py is the running
;               proof: per accel frame it runs signal-derivative (still/moving) + sequence-predictor (next state) through the
;               kernel, the predicted-vs-actual mismatch is the inference-error shown live, AND a nearest-shape CHALLENGER
;               runs the learning-arc.fk MECHANISM (intern an exemplar, recognize the nearest). HONEST SCOPE [experiments/
;               har-benchmark]: that live demo is the mechanism, NOT learning that generalizes — still/moving is a single
;               threshold (signal-derivative computes it by hand), the demo had no held-out test, 34 samples ~ 24s. On the
;               real UCI-HAR benchmark nearest-shape reaches ~81% (vs 18% floor, ~96% SOTA) but is a NON-PARAMETRIC memorizer
;               (model = the whole dataset). The "small model matches SOTA" prize (logistic reg: 3,372 params, 96%) needs a
;               PARAMETRIC model = integer `mul` in Form + quantized-int inference; that is the real lane, not nearest-shape.
;               The phone-native kernel is also BUILT (lane 8: libform_kernel_rust.so exports form_eval, ARM aarch64).
;               Remaining human-gated work is narrow: the JNI marshaling layer (jstring<->char*) so the .apk calls form_eval
;               on-device, and felt verification in the room.
;
; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
; THE CRITICAL PATH (what unblocks the most):
;   Lane 8 (one kernel arm on ARM + one sensor port) is the gate. It unblocks lane 4 (MediaSession), lane 7 (sensor leaves),
;   and the device half of lane 5. Lane 9's wire frames and lane 10's live wiring need no phone and can proceed in parallel.
;   So two fronts move at once: (A) the Android carrier build (toolchain -> JNI entry -> one arm -> one sensor), human-paced
;   because it needs hardware to verify; (B) the on-Mac runnable layer (lane 10 wiring + lane 9 wire frames), verifiable now.
;
; KIN: every lane's own .form holds its full teaching — recognition-router · perception-pipeline · self-grounding-perception ·
;   declared-source · shared-sensing · local-inference-as-organ · open-primitive-set · kernel-on-android · cell-sync-transport.
;   This file is only the map above them; when a lane's ground moves, update its four lines here so the map never lies.
